Coleophora squamosella is a moth of the family Coleophoridae. It is found in Europe (from Great Britain to Poland and Hungary and from Fennoscandia to France, Italy and Austria), the Baltic states, the Caucasus, Russia (Baikal and Altai) and Turkey.The wingspan is 11â€“13 mm. Adults are on wing in June and July.The larvae feed in a case on Erigeron species, including Erigeron acer.